Overview
HKSTP is an ecosystem of over 1000 technology companies. With the aim of growing more successful tech ventures, we are looking for an experienced and goal-oriented manager to drive their international expansion, by bringing in regional business opportunities, and to build a sophisticated overseas sales network. At the same time, attract high quality tech ventures from around the world to enrich our portfolio of high tech products and services, to meet our partners’ demand for innovative solutions.
Responsibilities:
Identify business opportunities actively in the region for tech ventures in HKSTP’s ecosystem;
Set up sales channels, strategies and implementation plan for identified overseas markets;
Lead the team to build a sophisticated network of regional sales partners such as sales reps, distributors and channel sales in selected industries;
Build strong and healthy sales pipelines;
Collect, consolidate and share insights in sales and product strategy with the tech ventures, and to prepare them for business matching;
Formulate promotion plan and outreaching programmes to maximize number of adoption cases and sales value;
Grow the number of tech ventures with innovative and high tech products/ services in our database; and
Perform any other duties as assigned by the management.
Requirements:
A bachelor’s degree or above in Business, Marketing, Communication or related disciplines;
Minimum 8 years of relevant experience in regional market development, preferably in innovation & technology sectors;
Experience in building and managing overseas B2B sales channels is essential;
A good team player with excellent interpersonal, communication and leadership skills to work with different teams within the organization;
Attention to details, strong analytical and problem-solving skills, self-motivated, organized, multi-tasking as well as able to work in a dynamic environment and under pressure with tight schedule; and
Proficiency in both written and spoken English and Chinese with good presentation skills; and
Frequent travel is expected.
Candidate with less experience will be considered for lower position.
We offer market competitive compensation, 5-day work week, and generous benefits including medical and life insurance; and voluntary contribution in addition to the legal minimum MPF.  To apply, please send your full resume with current and expected salary to the Human Resources & Office Administration Department, Hong Kong Science and Technology Parks Corporation, 5/F, Building 5E, 5 Science Park East Avenue, Hong Kong Science Park, Hong Kong or, by email via "Apply Now" on or before 27 January 2022.   Please quote the reference number on the email subject/envelope and the application letter. 
Personal data provided will be treated in strict confidence and used for recruitment purpose only.  All personal data collected will be used strictly in accordance with employer’s personal data policies, you can access to HKSTP’s Personal Information Collection Statement at https://www.hkstp.org/hkstp_web/en/hkstp/personal-information-collection-statement-recruitment
Applicants not invited for interview within four weeks after application deadline may consider their applications unsuccessful.  Personal data of unsuccessful applicants will be retained for a maximum of two years. 
